title: Scooby-Doo! Music of the Vampire
description: Daphne stars in a vampire movie. But when a real vampire shows up, the Scooby gang must investigate.

title: Come Undone
description: It's the end of the world! And our heroes must work together to ultimately realize their love for each other is the true Heart of the Jaguar.

title: Dance of the Undead
description: When Crystal Cove's favorite southern celebrity chef has a cooking accident, strange incidents ensue.

title: Heart of Evil
description: Dr. Zin, of Jonny Quest fame, wreaks havoc on Crystal Cove.

title: Scooby-Doo! and Kiss Rock and Roll Mystery
description: When a ghoul begins to terrorize an amusement park, the Mystery Inc. gang come head to head with the legendary rock group, KISS, who claim they're also there to solve the mystery. Now the two groups must learn to work together as the clues lead them on a cosmic journey to another dimension.

title: Ghost of the Red Baron
description: The members of Mystery, Inc. join with the Three Stooges to thwart the ghost of the Red Baron, a daring evildoer who has scared away all of farmer Sawyer's crop-dusting pilots in an effort to pressure Sawyer into leaving his land.

title: The Night the Clown Cried II: Tears of Doom
description: Crybaby Clown is back with a vengeance. He's kidnapping all sorts of folks all over Crystal Cove - namely a therapist, a hairdresser, a plastic surgeon and a publicist!

title: Scooby-Doo Meets the Addams Family
description: Scooby and the gang consent to spend the weekend as housekeepers in the spooky home of the Addams Family so Morticia and Gomez Addams can take a much needed vacation in Okeefenokee swamp.

title: The Exterminator
description: Scooby and the gang stop on Sunset Boulevard to help troubled motorist Don Adams. But the engine is infested with some vengeful, metal-munching termites that completely devour the motor. Scooby and the gang volunteer to help Adams with his next exterminator job.

title: The Frickert Fracas
description: When Jonathan Winters invites Scooby and the gang to stay at the farm of his friend, Maude Frickert, they mistakenly believe it will be a vacation from haunted houses and spooky characters. They soon learn differently when vandalizing scoundrels and truly scary scarecrows overrun Maude's farm.

title: The Night the Clown Cried
description: With the gang split up, Crystal Cove is being tormented by an evil-man-baby called Crybaby Clown!

title: Scooby-Doo and the Witch's Ghost
description: When the gang meets up with famous fright-writer Ben Ravencroft, he invited them to New England for his hometown's bit Autumn Harvest Festival. Things take a supernatural detour when they learn the place is haunted by Ben's ancestor Sarah! Will the mystery reveal that Sarah was a good-hearted healer or a spell-casting witch? Before you can say, "Scooby Snacks", the gang is on the case tangling with bumbling mummies, monster turkeys and (zoinks) a ghostly secret hidden in the Ravencroft family's past! Grooving to the tunes of the movie's rocking band The Hex Girls, it's Scooby-Doo at his spellbinding, spine-tingling, super-sleuthing best!

title: A Good Medium Is Rare
description: The gang finds a dog with a diamond collar. They return the dog to the owner, Phyllis Diller, who lives in an old, creepy house. Scooby and friends tour the home and discover it is apparently haunted by Phyllis' ex-husbands. Scooby unravels the mystery of these strange occurrences.

title: The Devouring
description: A famous band, whose members died 30 years ago in a plane crash in Crystal Cove, comes back to haunt the town on the 30th anniversary of their death.

title: Theater of Doom
description: Life imitates art in Crystal Cove's annual Haunted Historical Pageant.

title: Night on Haunted Mountain
description: When Ethan and Gary are mountain climbing Mount Diabla out in the desert, they're attacked by Lilith, a dark-winged angel of destruction.

title: Scooby-Doo and the Reluctant Werewolf
description: Scooby and Shaggy become race car drivers at the annual Monster Rally when the vampire, Dracula, hatches a plot to create a new werewolf. The pair encounter a host of classic horror-movie monsters in their attempt to stop Dracula.

title: Scarebear
description: The mayor of Crystal Cove has his camping trip ruined by the evil Scarebear and the gang is on the case.

title: Dark Night of the Hunters
description: Searching for the Heart of the Jaguar, the Mystery Incorporated gang heads down south of the border.

title: Scooby-Doo Meets Laurel and Hardy
description: Scooby and the gang join wits with Laurel and Hardy, newly appointed bellhops at a Vermont ski lodge, to track an abominable snowman by the name of Bigfoot!

title: The Gathering Gloom
description: When the gang is at Crystal Cove Cemetery watching a free screening of an old Vincent Van Ghoul movie with half the town, they are attacked by the Graveyard Ghoul!

title: The Haunted Showboat
description: Scooby-Doo and the gang, along with the rock group Josie and the Pussycats, battle ghosts haunting the Dixie Queen Showboat on the Missouri River. The mystery begins when the 100-year-old ghost of Injun Joe, a Mark Twain character from Tom Sawyer, along with another ghost, drag chains, move objects and make scary noises.

title: Stand and Deliver
description: A dandy, well-groomed, 18th century Englishman haunts the highways of Crystal Cove.

title: The Haunted Candy Factory
description: Cass Elliot, former singer with The Mamas and the Papas, hires Scooby-Doo and the Mystery, Inc. kids to investigate two living globs of green cotton candy creating a sticky mess at her Sugarplum Candy Company.

title: House of the Nightmare Witch
description: A Russian museum exhibit comes to life. It's an evil Russian witch by the name of Baba Yaga. The gang hunts Baba Yaga in Crystal Cove's Haunted Forest of Doom only to end up being the hunted.

title: The Caped Crusader Caper
description: Scooby and Mystery Inc. meet the terrible twosome, Penguin and Joker, on a camping trip in the forest. To stop the evildoers, the kids enlist the aid of those crusaders against crime, Batman and Robin. Penguin and Joker plan to steal the newest invention of Professor Flakey, a flying suit but Scooby and Shaggy's bumbling antics foil the criminals' scheme.

title: The Horrible Herd
description: A heard of supernatural skull cattle wreak havoc on Crystal Cove.

title: The Haunted Horseman in Hagglethorn Hall
description: The gang must prove a ghostly horseman haunting Hagglethorn Castle is a fake apparition. Otherwise, Davy Jones' uncle will have to sell the Scottish fortress, once a thriving tourist spot, to the greedy Duke of Strathmore.

title: Grim Judgement
description: Hebediah Grim, a menacing Puritannical ancestor of Crystal Cove, terrorizes Lovers Lane.

title: Through the Curtain
description: Traveling through the underground caverns, our heroes trail Pericles and company.

title: The Ghostly Creep from the Deep
description: The members of Mystery, Inc. join forces with the Harlem Globetrotters on the eerie banks of a haunted swamp to battle supernatural spirits unleashed by the ghost of Redbeard the pirate!

title: The Hodag of Horror
description: A traveling curio wagon arrives in Crystal Cove and a carnie-barker by the name of Gene Shepherd unveils the Hodag, a beast supposed to be found in the wilds of Wisconsin. It's a horrible fake. But when it comes to life and starts stealing, the gang investigates.

title: Scooby-Doo Meets Jeannie
description: On a trip back in time, Scooby and the gang meet a genie, Jeannie, as they travel to Persia to help a prince fight evil ghosts. They learn of a legend many thousands of years ago of an ancestor of the prince imprisoned an evil Jinn in a bottle. Now, with the assistance of the prince's greedy uncle, the vengeful genie initiates a sinister plan to scare the prince into abandoning the palace.

title: The Midnight Zone
description: When the DJ at the local radio station, K-GHOUL, is attacked, the gang investigates.

title: Wrath of the Krampus
description: When the strange appearance of a mean goat-man demon named Krampus terrorizes naughty kids all over town, the Mystery Inc. gang decide to look into things. Chasing Krampus all over Crystal Cove, they try to second-guess the crazy, evil goat-man's motives and who could be behind the mystery.

title: Ghastly Ghost Town
description: After a king-sized bat forces the Mystery Machine into a sandpit, Scooby and the gang cross the desert on foot seeking help. Soon, they meet the Three Stooges, who are actually the ones in need of help!

title: The Phantom of the Country Music Hall
description: An exciting evening at the Grand Old Opry in Nashville proves to be almost too exciting when a mysterious phantom appears. It's a haunting experience for the members of Mystery, Inc. when they must search for their missing friend, country singer Jerry Reed.

title: Guess Who's Knott Coming to Dinner
description: When the hopelessly lost members of Mystery, Inc. enter Moody Manor to ask for directions, Don Knotts, the world's greatest detective, mistakenly believes they are the relatives of the estate's wealthy late owner. Don suspects one of them murdered Captain Moody!

title: The Lochness Mess
description: When Scooby-Doo and the kids travel to a small New England town to visit Shaggy's Uncle Nathaniel, they plunge into a maelstrom of mystery, encounter the ghost of Paul Revere and confront a spooky sea serpent! With the aid of the Harlem Globetrotters, who are vacationing nearby, the kids discover the actual culprit.

title: Gates of Gloom
description: Professor Pericles and what's left of his Mystery Incorporated are looking for the entrance into the caverns, where the cursed treasure and the Evil Entity are buried.

title: Aliens Among Us
description: The gang investigates some potential extra-terrestrial life in Crystal Cove with the help of Velma's mother.

title: The Mystery of Haunted Island
description: The Harlem Globetrotters and Scooby and his friends are hijacked to a haunted island for an experience they will never forget. Taking refuge in an old mansion, they witness statues moving, leaving behind luminous footprints and handprints! Following the clues, the kids eventually emerge from the haunted house and discover the truth.

title: Scooby-Doo! Stage Fright
description: Join Scooby-Doo, Shaggy and the Mystery Inc. crew as they head to Chicago for a talent show, a few museum tours and whole lot of pizza!

title: Scooby-Doo and the Alien Invaders
description: Late one night in the desert, the Mystery Machine van breaks down after it is forced off the road by what appears to be a UFO. Locals confirm the sighting, telling the gang about a nearby government project searching for extraterrestrial intelligence. While waiting for the van to be repaired, Scooby and Shaggy are abducted by 8-foot green aliens. They awaken from the frightening experience back out in the desert with a beautiful free-lance photographer named Crystal and her dog, Amber. Together, they uncover the secret of the aliens, falling in love in the process.

title: Web of the Dreamweaver
description: A rash of strange crimes happen when a number of prominent Crystal Cove citizens destroy the things they love most - a car, a house, a food empire. The gang investigates and soon discovers each of these citizens had a dream wherein the Dreamweaver, a horrible goblin-king, told them to do it.

title: Night Terrors
description: When a visiting family finds some terrifying specters in an old library high in the hills above Crystal Cove, the gang investigates.

title: The Spirited Spooked Sports Show
description: Tim Conway, a coach at Velma's alma mater, enlists Scooby and the gang to eliminate ghosts haunting the debt-ridden school. The only opportunity to raise money for the school, the All Sports Benefit Show, has been postponed because no teams will play in the haunted high school and people refuse to attend any event held there.

title: Art of Darkness!
description: World-renowned modern artist Randy Warsaw is Crystal Cove's greatest art treasure. But when Warsaw's greatest work of art, Junk, comes to life and tries to destroy Warsaw, Mayor Nettles asks the gang to investigate.

title: The Secret of Shark Island
description: Scooby-Doo and the gang give singers Sonny and Cher a ride after their car breaks down in a fierce storm. The kids take the two performers to the rambling, run-down Hideaway Hotel, an off-season beach retreat, where they have planned a delayed honeymoon away from the crowds. But soon, strange happenings interrupt the couple's happiness, and Scooby and the gang investigate.

title: The Man in the Mirror
description: In the basement of a local haunted mansion, the gang finds a strange mirror with a mind of its own.

title: Scooby-Doo! Curse of the Lake Monster
description: While heading to a country club owned by Daphne's uncle, the Mystery Inc. gang stumbles onto strange happenings. The pals need to work summer jobs. After hearing a dire warning, the friends dismiss it until a frog monster attacks.

title: Weird Winds of Winona
description: After the Mystery Machine breaks down in Winona, Mississippi, Scooby and the gang join forces with Speed Buggy and his buddies to quell the mysterious midnight winds that spook the inhabitants of the tiny village.

title: Scooby-Doo Meets Dick Van Dyke
description: Dick Van Dyke purchases a carnival and names it the Dick Van Dyke Barrel of Fun. But the place isn't fun. It's haunted! Scooby and the gang, who take a night off from chasing spooks to visit the carnival, help Dick uncover the apparitions that are scaring away both customers and employees.

title: The Spooky Fog
description: A unique form of small-town hospitality awaits Scooby and the gang. Police officer Don Knotts invites them to spend the night in the finest accommodations in Juneberry, the local jail! But soon, the kids help Don solve the mystery of the spooky fog.

title: Scooby-Doo! Frankencreepy
description: Velma discovers she's inherited her great-great-uncle Dr. Von Dinkenstein's cursed castle in the terrifying town of Transylvania Pennsylvania, that is. Just when the Gang persuades Velma to go claim her inheritance, the ghost of Dinkenstein Castle blows up the Mystery Machine as a warning! Now the Crew must spring back into action, but this time it's personal! Who's responsible for the Dinkenstein monster? What family secret has Velma been hiding? Will Fred recover from the loss of his beloved Mystery Machine? Can any helpless snack survive Scooby and Shaggy's monster-sized appetites?

title: Nightmare in Red
description: Our heroes allow themselves to be hypnotized so that they can enter the dreamworld.
